INSERT INTO txt VALUES (134,'It\'s time to kick-off the 2005 Vanguard 15 Racing Season on San\nFrancisco Bay! The first regatta of the season will be the St.\nFrancis Spring Dinghy on March 12-13. Please register with St.\nFrancisc by March 9th to recieve the early bird deal of $50 ($5 off\nfor US Sailing Membership) after March 9th the cost will be $60 ($5\nof with US Sailing Membership). Make sure that not only do you\nregister with St. Francis but you also sign up on the Vanguard 15\nwebsite (www.vanguard15.org). The NOR is posted at\nhttp://www.stfyc.com/Files/2005%20Spring%20Dinghy%20Notice%20of%20Rac\ne.pdf and the entry form is at\nhttp://www.stfyc.com/Files/SPRING%20DINGHY%20INVITATIONAL%20Entry%20F\norm.pdf. \n\nSince this will be a trailering regatta please email me and let me\nknow if you are able to tow your own boat or if you need somebody to\ntow for you. Also let me know if you can piggy back boats for others.\n(towing will done with a car, not likely done with a boat). \n\nAfter racing St. Francis will be having a social event with free\nchili, beer, and soda. There will also be a cash bar. Once the beer\nruns out at St Francis head over to Rolf Kaiser\'s house for more\nbeer/soda, music and eventually make it up to Mauna Loa (maybe). His\nhouse is a few blocks from St. Francis. His house is in the middle of\nconstruction so ignore the dust. He will have the grill going so come\nover and celebrate the start of the season with friends. Even if you\nare not sailing come on over. Please email me if you are interested\nand I will send you directions. \n\nThis is one of the best regattas of the season so I expect to see\neveryone out there! I garantee you will have a great time on the city\nfront! ');
