INSERT INTO txt VALUES (170,'Hey Vanguardians \n\nAs many of you are involved with the programs at TISC most of you are\nfamiliar with giving back to the sailing community and fostering the\nnext generation of sailors. Well here is your next opportunity. This\nlast weekend Marin Catholic High School competed in the High School\nPCC\'s and finished third overall. This qualifies them for the high\nSchool National Championships which are being held in less than a\nmonth in V15\'s. As an on the water judge for the PCC\'s, I can tell\nyou that these young people are exceptional sailors. They may even be\nable to give some of you a run for your money. The MC team includes\nSean Kelly, Kristen Rittenhouse, Myles Gutenkunst, Delaney Lynch, and\nMichaela McCloskey ( not only are they great sailors but they are\ngreat kids as well, I have know them all since they were in opti\'s).\nThe kids usually only practice in CFJ\'s and don\'t have any experience\nin V15s. I have mentioned to the kids that they should come over and\npractice on Thursday nights but they will need two boats to practice\nin and hopefully a V15 Rockstar who would be willing to show them the\ntricks of the V15. As the only Bay Area team to make the cut, it\nwould be great to help give these kids the competitive edge to help\nthem succeed at nationals. Please let me know if you would be willing\nto lend your boat or show these kids the best way to make the boats\ngo fast. If you do decide to lend your boat be assured that I will be\nthere to supervise and make sure they take good care of your stuff.\nAny help would be greatly appreciated. On behalf of the MC sailing\nteam, thank you - Vikki Fennell ');
