INSERT INTO txt VALUES (196,'Part of Vanguard\'s continuous improvement program includes the\nongoing evaluation of the many new material innovations and\nmanufacturing process advancements in the composite materials\nindustry. Our aim is to deliver the most durable and exciting\nproducts for our customers. Vanguard is now introducing a refinement\nof the V15 construction that has increased the boat\'s durability\nwithout adding any weight. The hull is now significantly stronger\nand the deck is more resistant to pressure dings. We wanted to point\nout that this improvement yields a slightly more noticeable \"print\nthrough\" or pattern in the finish of the hull. However, we are\nconfident that the advantages gained with this change far outweigh\nthe slightly more noticeable print through. \r\n\r\nNed Jones \n\nProduct Manager \n\nVanguard Sailboats \n\n401.683.0960 ');
INSERT INTO txt VALUES (197,'- Toss Fleet Captain Jim Barkow and crew Mallory into the Cove for their win at PCC\'s\r\n- Story time highlights from Ski Sail\r\n- The KTVU-2 helicopter and the KRON-4 film crew will be on location\r\n- Great post-race food including steak sandwiches, chili, lobster bisque, fresh calamari, and jumbo shrimp....or...maybe...just...pretzels\r\n- Show Geoff, Kara, Madhavan, and Taylor what they have been missing the last five weeks\r\n- Boat races on land can be even more fun than the water (and may count toward your final score)\r\n- There are 14 more minutes of sunlight this Thursday than last - obviously enough time to get in 6 races this week\r\n- Can the Laser fleet rally with a great turnout?\r\n- Can the V15 fleet break it\'s all time record of 26 boats for a Thursday night set back in 2002?\r\n- Can DJ Dave Byron mix some post race tunes?\r\n- Can we convince Matt Gregory to change his plane ticket back to one of those flyover states?\r\n- How-many-cups-of-beer-does-the-keg-hold contest?  \r\n- Name-The-Baby-Washington contest!\r\n- Who will win the 40\' Protector in the Grand Prize drawing?\r\n- What will Russell Coutts have to say after the races about crewing for Madhavan?\r\n- Will Team Waypoint Pizza make an appearance?  \r\n- Will the Sellers\', Horsch\'s, and Bennett\'s get a babysitter? \r\n- Will you make the highlights in Jay Palace\'s Friday re-cap email?\r\n- Will Method install soap dispensers at the hoists for do-it-yourself showers?\r\n- Will somebody cave in to host the post-venue party location (everyone...\"Rolf, Rolf, Rolf, Rolf, Rolf...\")?\r\n- The Thursday forecast is sun, sunny, more sun, and 76 degrees\r\n');
