INSERT INTO txt VALUES (276,'Greetings Vanguardians, \n\nThe V15 Bay Champs will be held out of TISC on the weekend of August\n13-14 and will feature a morning racing clinic on both Saturday and\nSunday from 9am to 12pm. Regatta racing will start at 1pm each day. I\nwill teach the clinic and it is included in the entry fee for the\nevent. I will cover setup, boat handling, boat speed, tactics and\nstrategy during the clinic hours and it will feature both on shore\nand on the water instruction. We will also de-brief after racing each\nday to help spread the knowledge of the top teams. There will be a\nBBQ at TISC on Saturday after racing (included in the entry fee). \r\n\r\nI will send the NOR/Entry Form as a .pdf file via a separate email.\nCompetitors that fax their entry to me prior to 12pm on Friday,\nAugust 12th, will receive a $10 discount on their entry fee. If you\nplan on sailing, please sign up on the website as well: \n\nhttp://www.vanguard15.org/schedule/?r=228 \r\n\r\nI need some help with running the clinic and RC for the event. If you\ncan help out, please drop me an email or give me a call. \r\n\r\nThanks, \r\n-Nick\r\n\r\nNick Adamson \n\njnadamson@yahoo.com \n\n415-706-3250 (cell) ');
INSERT INTO txt VALUES (277,'Svendsen\'s Boat Works has generously offered to sponsor the Vanguard\n15 Bay Champs next weekend (August 13-14)! Thanks to Alex and Sean\nfor sponsoring the Saturday night BBQ and keg AND coming up with a\ngreat assortment of trophy prizes including a Tack-Tick Micro\nCompass, Lotus Life Preservers, Harken Sunglasses and Sandals! The\nevent now has a morning racing clinic with some of the fleet\'s top\nsailors, great racing in the afternoon, a BBQ/keg party on Saturday,\nand awesome prizes! \r\n\r\nNow\'s the time to find that partner and start making plans to attend!\nDon\'t have a partner but want to sail? Sign up as an individual on\nthe website page \n\n(http://www.vanguard15.org/schedule/?r=228) and make a note of what\nyou need to get on the water. In case you missed the last one, the\nNOR and Entry form will be sent via a separate email today. Those\nthat want to get the pre-registration rate ($30 for USSA \n\nmembers) need to fax their entry forms to 650-598-0454 by 12pm on\nFriday, August 12th. \r\n\r\nLet me know if you have any questions. \r\n\r\nThanks, \r\n-Nick\r\n\r\nNick Adamson \n\njnadamson@yahoo.com \n\n415-706-3250 (cell) ');
