INSERT INTO txt VALUES (316,'Notice of Race \r\n\r\n1.0 RULES \r\n\r\n1.1 The regatta will be governed by the Racing Rules of Sailing (RRS)\nfor 2005-2008, the 2005-2008 US SAILING prescriptions, the 2003 Laser\nClass Rules, the 2001 Vanguard 15 Class Rules, this Notice of Race\nand the Sailing Instructions. \r\n\r\n1.2 RRS 40.1 will be changed as follows: All competitors are required\nto wear life-jackets or other adequate personal buoyancy while\nracing, the Y will not be displayed. \r\n\r\n1.3 Competitors in all classes are REQUIRED to carry a bowline\n(painter) of at least 15 feet attached to a towing point while\nracing. \r\n\r\n\r\n2.0 ELIGIBILITY AND ENTRY \r\n\r\n2.1 The following classes are invited to participate: Vanguard 15,\nLaser (full rig) and Laser Radial. \r\n\r\n2.2 Eligible boats may enter by completing the form on the day of the\nrace. \r\n\r\n2.3 All sailors MUST have a current TISC Medical & Liability Form on\nfile BEFORE racing. \r\n\r\n\r\n3.0 FEES \r\n\r\n3.1 Entry fee is $15.00 per day raced, payable in cash or check made\nout to Catherine King \r\n\r\n3.2 Boats that do not pay will not be scored. \r\n\r\n\r\n4.0 SCHEDULE \r\n\r\n4.1 Racing will be held on Saturdays, January 28, February 25, and\nMarch 25, 2006 \r\n\r\n4.2 Pre-registration is encouraged on the Vanguard 15 website\n(www.vanguard15.org) \r\n\r\n4.3 Registration will be held from 12:00-12:30pm in TISC Club House \r\n\r\n4.4 Sailors Meeting will be held at 12:30pm in front of TISC Club\nHouse \r\n\r\n4.5 First Warning will be at 1:00pm \r\n\r\n4.5.1 Vanguard 15 class: goal of 5 or more races per day \r\n\r\n4.5.2 Laser classes: goal of 5 races per day \r\n\r\n4.6 Award Ceremony will follow the conclusion of racing each day \r\n\r\n\r\n5.0 SAILING INSTRUCTIONS \r\n\r\n5.1 The Sailing Instructions will be available at registration and\nduring the Sailors Meeting. \n\n5.2 All changes to the Sailing Instructions will be stated orally at\nthe Sailors Meeting. \r\n\r\n\r\n6.0 RACING AREA & COURSES \r\n\r\n6.1 The intended racing area will be Clipper Cove, utilizing orange\nball marks. \r\n\r\n6.2 Single or double windward-leeward courses will be used. \r\n\r\n6.3 The 3 minute Sound-Signal Starting System (Appendix Q) will be\nused without visual signals. \r\n\r\n\r\n7.0 SCORING & AWARDS \r\n\r\n7.1 The Low Point Scoring System in Appendix A of the racing rules\nwill be used. \n\n7.2 Rule 4.2 will apply for daily award calculation. Rule A9 will\napply for overall award calculation. \r\n\r\n7.3 Daily awards will be given for first-third place in all classes;\noverall awards will be given for first-third place in the Vanguard 15\nclass and presented at the Annual Meeting in December. \r\n\r\n\r\n8.0 REGATTA CONTACT \r\n\r\n8.1 Catherine King, Regatta Chair, at (916) 752-5802 or\nsailflat@earthlink.net \r\n\r\n8.2 Vanguard 15 Fleet 53 website, www.vanguard15.org ');
