INSERT INTO txt VALUES (368,'Dan L., TISC Ops Manager, has the ramp and more dock space in\nservice, effective immediately. So, you will be able to dolly launch\nthis coming Thursday Night! \r\n\r\nPlease remember when launching from the ramp to move your boat over\nto the last available slot to finish rigging. This avoids\nbottlenecking the launching queue. \r\n\r\nAlso, ALL boats MUST have an ATTACHED PAINTER or BOW-LINE that is 15\nFEET OR MORE. \r\n-This is a SAFETY REQUIREMENT.  So, go to West Marine or Svenson\'s and get some more line if your painter is too short or has disappeared from your boat.  \r\n-This is a MANDATORY safety requirement, just as PFDs are mandatory on-the-water.\r\n\r\nReminders: \r\n\r\n1. Race fees are $100/season or $15/night \r\n\r\n2. Make checks payable to: V15 Fleet 53 or use the Paypal option,\ncontact Adam Spiegel (Treasurer) for information on this option \r\n\r\n3. V15 skippers also need to pay $25 for fleet dues. A combined\npayment is acceptable \r\n\r\n4. Checks should be given to Catherine King (Race Chair) or Adam\nSpiegel (V15 Treasurer) when you register \r\n\r\n5. Sail numbers & race results will NOT be posted if payment is not\nmade \r\n-----\r\n6. Main sails need to display the REGISTERED SAIL NUMBER, not a\ntemporary sail number, unless cleared through Race Chairs...Catherine\nor Sarah (not Race Committee) \r\n-----\r\n7. All registered boats are expected to host one Thursday Night as\nSocial Chair. \r\n-Assignments will be made by the Race Chairs (see Catherine King).  \r\n-You are responsible for finding a replacement Social Chair, if you cannot host your assigned night \r\n----- \r\n8. All sailors are invited to participate in the post-racing social\nactivities. \r\n-Nightly scores will be announced as soon as possible after all protest hearings have been concluded  \r\n-V15 scores will be posted to the V15 website as soon as possible  \r\n-----\r\n9. Sarah Deeds (Race Chair) will be explaining and reviewing the 3\nMinute Justice protest system used for this series. \r\n-Sailing is a self-regulating sport and mistakes will happen on the race course. Thus, protesting is a normal element of sail boat racing.\r\n\r\n-Please review the rules and honor the spirit of them.  If you make a mistake, do your penalty turn(s).  \r\n\r\n-If you want to protest another boat\'s actions, remember to yell \"protest\" (not \"do your circles,\" etc.).\r\n\r\n-You must tell the RC at the end of the race if you will be protesting a boat through the 3 minute justice system.\r\n\r\n-No forms/written protest are required for the 3 minute justice system.\r\n-----\r\n10. Once registered, a boat only needs to SIGN-IN each night with the\nRace Chairs to have their scores posted. Please remind skippers who\nborrow your boat about this requirement. \r\n\r\nposted on April 1, 2006 by Catherine King ');
