INSERT INTO txt VALUES (432,'Summer Sailstice is a worldwide celebration of the sailing\nexperience, and this year, the Treasure Island Sailing Center (TISC)\nhas teamed up with Summer Sailstice to create a community-wide\nsailing event for the entire San Francisco Bay. The weekend will\ninclude a 2-day regatta and a Saturday late afternoon party for\nracers, cruisers and TISC supporters. Proceeds of the weekend will\nsupport the many successful outreach sailing programs offered at\nTISC, including youth camps and classes and adaptive sailing programs\nfor people with developmental and physical disabilities. \r\n\r\nMain website:\nhttp://www.tisailing.org/sailstice06/index.cfm/display/1 \r\n\r\nREGATTA INFORMATION \r\n-Racing for 420\'s, Lasers/Radials, and Vanguard 15\'s will be in the Emeryville Flats just northeast of Clipper Cove (Course Bravo)\r\n-$70 per boat for Vanguard 15 (includes 2 tickets for the Summer Sailstice Saturday celebration)...Members of US Sailing may deduct $5.00 from the entry fee. Include copy of USSA Membership Card with entry.\r\n-Continental Breakfast will be available Saturday and Sunday mornings for competitors and volunteers. \r\n-The Saturday Sailstice festivities includes dinner, drinks, and live music. \r\n-There will also be a silent auction and raffle to raise funds for the Youth and Adaptive Outreach Sailing Programs held at TISC. \r\n-Extra tickets for family and friends can be purchased for $25 per person. Children are our guests! \r\n');
