INSERT INTO venue VALUES (14,'Inverness Yacht Club','To reach the park via Sir Francis Drake Blvd. you will want to travel\r\nnorthbound on Highway 101 across the Golden Gate Bridge. After about 20\r\nminutes (with light traffic) you\'ll pass by exits for Sausalito, Marin City,\r\nand Mill Valley. As you pass through the following town of Corte Madera, you\r\nshould see an exit for San Anselmo on the right side of the freeway. This is\r\nthe exit you\'ll want to take and it will come quickly so be prepared. Upon\r\ntaking this exit you will come to a 2-way stop - you should take a left hand\r\nturn. This will put you onto Sir Francis Drake Blvd. towards San Anselmo -\r\nthe same route you\'ll take to the park. You are now on Sir Francis Drake and\r\nwill want to stay on it for close to 30-40 minutes from the 101 turn off.\r\nYou will pass through the towns of Kentfield, San Anselmo, Fairfax, San\r\nGeronimo, Woodacre, and other towns on your way to the park. About 30 - 35\r\nminutes from the 101/Sir Francis Drake exit you will pass through Samuel P.\r\nTaylor State Park. After passing through this beautiful park you drive up\r\nand over a relatively short hill and come to a stop light. This is the town\r\nof Olema. You\'ll need to take a right turn here at the light onto Highway 1.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nFrom here you are close to Inverness Yacht Club which is at 28750 Sir\r\nFrancis Drake Blvd. in Inverness. According to Yahoo Maps: after you turn\r\nright on highway 1, you go 2 miles and turn left onto Sir Francis Drake.\r\nYacht club should be on your right after 4.4 miles. Tomales Bay should be on\r\nyour right. I do not warrrant that these directions are correct since Yahoo\r\nMaps aren\'t always correct.',NULL,'www.invernessyachtclub.org','','','','',20011002164916);
